content: Certainly! Bob Dylan's electric performance at the Newport Folk Festival in 1965 is a pivotal moment in music history. During the performance, Dylan was backed by a rock band (including future members of The Band) and played a set that included iconic songs like "Maggie's Farm," "Like a Rolling Stone," and "It Takes a Lot to Laugh, It Takes a Train to Cry." "Maggie's Farm" is a particularly well-known song from this performance, and it's a great example of Dylan's transition from acoustic folk to electric rock. Overall, the entire set is worth a listen for any music fan.
